// For reference - Default Shadertoy "Image" source before 2018
/*

void mainImage( out vec4 fragColor, in vec2 fragCoord )
{
	vec2 uv = fragCoord.xy / iResolution.xy;
	fragColor = vec4(uv,0.5+0.5*sin(iTime),1.0);
}

*/

// Original Shader Description
/*
Shadertoy works by appending a text footer to the editable source, containing a definition of main with a line similar to
[code]mainImage(outColor, gl_FragCoord.xy);[/code]
Therefore mainImage may be provided as a preprocessor definition.
*/

/*

First created on 2017-07-12, this shader is the beginning of the
'#define mainImage' trick on Shadertoy, unless there exists one from before the
SH17A competition.

Likely the trick has been discovered many times, as there are other shaders
from before 2020-07-18 that use it.

Take a look at Shadertoy's GLSL header and footer in effect.js for similar
ideas:
    https://www.shadertoy.com/js/effect.js
Note, however, that many possible tricks are very likely to stop working at
some point in Shadertoy's future as these components evolve.  For all serious
shaders (including compact/'golf' code), please use the standard function
definition.

As of 2020-11-07, the shader main function, where mainImage is invoked, has
been moved to the header code prepended to shaders, so the '#define mainImage'
trick no longer works.

 - Theron Tarigo (ttg)
   Updated 2020-11-07

*/
